Name: chronic tic disorder
Definition: A tic disorder that is characterized by single or multiple motor or phonic tics
Synonym: chronic motor or vocal tic disorder

Name: Gilles de la Tourette syndrome
Definition: A tic disorder that is characterized by multiple physical (motor) tics and at least one vocal (phonic) tic present for more than a year.

Name: obsolete neck cancer
Definition: A tic disorder that is characterized by multiple physical (motor) tics and at least one vocal (phonic) tic present for more than a year.

Name: transient tic disorder
Definition: A tic disorder that consists of multiple motor and/or phonic tics with duration of at least 4 weeks
